Consider the following program segment for concurrent processing using semaphore operators P and V for synchronization. Draw the precedence graph for the statements S1 to S9.

var a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h,i,j,k : semaphore;
begin
  cobegin
    begin S1; V(a); V(b) end;
    begin P(a); S2; V(c); V(d) end;
    begin P(c); S4; V(e) end;
    begin P(b); S3; V(f); V(g) end;
    begin P(d); P(f); S6; V(h) end;
    begin P(e); P(g); S7; V(i) end;
    begin P(h); P(i); S8 end;
    begin P(j); S5; V(j); V(k) end;
    begin P(k); S9 end;
  coend
end

Which of the following is the correct precedence relationship?
A. S1 must precede S2, S3, S4
B. S6 requires both S3 and S2 to complete
C. S8 requires S6 and S7 to complete
D. All of the above

